== Roasted Sweet Potato ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{1}(peeled and diced into ½-inch pieces). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Tomato Salsa ==

While sweet potato roasts, core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced). Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced); mince a few pieces until you have 1 TBSP. Dice @tomato{1}(diced). Finely chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}(finely chopped). Quarter @lime{1}(quartered).

Place ½ tsp @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step) in a small #bowl{} and reserve for Step 4.

== Cooked Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and diced onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once sweet potato is done, add to pan along with remaining southwest spice blend. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Turn off heat.

== Tomato Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

To bowl with reserved southwest spice blend, add @sour cream{3%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Quesadilla Assembly ==

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface.

In a second small bowl, combine @cheddar cheese{½%cup} and @mozzarella cheese{½%cup}.

Sprinkle half the cheese mixture onto one half of each tortilla. Top with cooked veggies, then sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

== Cooking Quesadillas ==

Wash out pan used for veggies. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Top with salsa and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.